   "description": "Thord Gösta Fredrik Edström was a Swedish director and forestry expert. He was born on July 15, 1901, in Frösö parish, Jämtland county, Sweden. He married Margit Griimisigård in 1932. He graduated from the forestry course at ISIKOGISIBÖIGISK in 1927. He was the executive director for the forestry association for southeastern Sweden, covering Kronoberg, Blekinge, Kalmar County south, North Kalmar County, and Östergötland. He was also a board member of various forestry companies and associations and received a KAK medal. He was a member of the Freemasons (VIL gr.) and wrote articles in newspapers and magazines. His hobby was reading books."
